{
  "texts": [
    "Learners of English as a Second/Foreign Language (ESL/EFL) have varying perspectives on the target language, its speakers, its culture, and its values.",
    "The learners\" attitudes influence the language and proficiency of the ESL/EFL learners.",
    "Since learning a language has a very close connection to the attitude one has toward a language, it is necessary to understand what the term symbolizes.",
    "To put it simply, one\"s attitude is one\"s behavior and one\"s way of looking at things.",
    "It refers to a feeling or opinion about something."
  ]
}